    "notes": "TECHNICAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nRecorded in Berkshire Performing Arts Center, Studio A, Lenox Massachusetts, April 13, 15, 1993\r\nMicrophones: Neumann M-50b (vacuun tube)\r\nOn-Stage Microphone Preamps: FM Acoustics M1 ClassAmp\r\nDigital Recording Processor: Telarc / Ultra-Analog 20-Bit 128 times oversampling A/D converter, custom engineered by Kenneth Hamann\r\nMicrophone, Interconnecting & Speaker Cables: This recording utilized the latest in cable technology including Monster Cable M1500, M1.5, Series I & III Prolink\r\nMonitor Speakers: Waveform Mach 7 (Bi-amplified) by Ötvös Industries\r\nPower Amplifiers: Bryston 4BPNB\r\nExclusive Control Room and Recording Hall Acoustic Treatment: RPG Abffusors & Diffusors\r\nDigital Editing: Sony DAE 3000\r\n\r\nDuring the recording of the digital masters and the subsequent transfer to disc, the signal was not passed through any processing device (i.e., compression, limiting, or equalization) at any step during production.\r\n\r\nSpecial thanks to James Sacksteder, Liz Thomson, Ken Amis, Doug Wright, The New Wordl Brass, John Hauser, David Cutler, Julie Pierfrit, Todd Murphy, Marily Najaime, Matt Carson, Egil Smedvig, The Cats, MTT for encouragement, Bob for letting me do this project, the whole crew at Telarc, but especially Kelly for a wonderful arrangement and helping me through this one. - Rolf Smedvig\r\n\r\n©℗1993 Telarc\r\nMade in Austria\r\nPrinted in U.S.A.\r\n",
